# Format: <CVE-ID>  # <reason>
# Trivy reads this file at the repo root for the workflow at .github/workflows/ci.yml.
# Re-evaluate every entry quarterly — delete it once a stable fix lands.
#
# Triage policy: we accept HIGH-severity CVEs that meet ALL of:
#   1. No fix is published on npm yet, OR the only fix is a major-version
#      bump that requires upstream parents (e.g. @nestjs/*, glob, chokidar)
#      to follow first.
#   2. Exposure is bounded by an existing control (auth, throttle, build-only
#      code path, or input that's already sanitized).
# We do NOT accept CRITICAL CVEs without a separate explicit decision.
#
# When a real-world exploit appears for any of these, escalate immediately
# regardless of "no fix" status.

# multer DoS via dropped/unhandled/malformed requests. Latest stable on npm
# is 2.1.1; @nestjs/platform-express resolves to 2.0.0 transitively. Fix
# versions in Trivy DB (2.0.1, 2.0.2, 2.1.0, 2.1.2) are partly unpublished
# and partly behind the @nestjs/platform-express peer pin. Storefront
# uploads hit @Throttle (60/60s) + an auth guard, so DoS surface is bounded.
# Drop these once @nestjs/platform-express bumps multer or 2.1.2+ ships.
CVE-2025-48997
CVE-2025-7338
CVE-2026-2359
CVE-2026-3304
CVE-2026-3520

# tar arbitrary-file CVEs. Direct override forces installed tar to 7.5.13;
# Trivy still flags the dep-spec strings inside transitive package.json
# files (e.g. node-pre-gyp's "tar": "^6.x") even though the resolved version
# is the safe one. This is a Trivy reporting artifact, not a real exposure.
# Drop when Trivy stops reading dep specs as "installed".
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802

# minimatch DoS via crafted glob patterns. Ships transitively via glob/
# rimraf/etc. Used at build time and shutdown only, never on a request hot
# path. Fix requires bumping all consumers (glob, rimraf, micromatch...).
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# picomatch ReDoS via crafted extglob patterns. Fix exists in 3.x and 4.x
# but those are breaking releases consumed by chokidar/glob — forcing them
# via overrides regressed @nestjs/* peers locally. Build/dev-time path.
CVE-2026-33671

# fast-xml-parser DoS via unlimited XML entity expansion / specially crafted
# input. Comes in via @aws-sdk/* (S3 signed URLs). Fix is a major bump on
# @aws-sdk that we'll do as part of task #33 (AWS Secrets Manager) when we
# audit the SDK surface anyway.
CVE-2026-26278
CVE-2026-33036
CVE-2026-25896

# glob command injection via malicious patterns. Same family as minimatch
# above — consumed at build/dev time only. Pinning glob >=10.5.0 requires
# every parent to follow.
CVE-2025-64756

# jws improper signature verification. Comes in via passport-jwt; we sign
# our own JWTs with RS256 and never accept tokens generated by jws's
# vulnerable code path. Real fix is bumping passport-jwt itself.
CVE-2025-65945

# lodash arbitrary code execution via untrusted input. We import lodash
# only transitively (graphql-codegen and friends, dev-time). No prod code
# path passes user input into lodash sinks. Drop when 4.18.0 ships and
# parents follow.
CVE-2026-4800

# @apollo/server DoS via startStandaloneServer. We never start Apollo
# standalone — the GraphQL endpoint is mounted via @nestjs/apollo (Nest's
# Express driver). The vulnerable code path is unreachable in this app.
# Drop when @apollo/server >=4.13.0 is pulled in by @nestjs/apollo.
CVE-2026-23897

# @nestjs/microservices DoS via recursive handleData in JsonSocket TCP
# transport. We never bind a TCP microservice — RabbitMQ goes through
# amqp-connection-manager directly, not Nest's transport. Fix is a major
# bump to 11.x which would force the entire @nestjs/* stack with it; we
# defer that to its own task. The vulnerable code path is unreachable.
CVE-2026-40879

# cross-spawn ReDoS. We force-resolve to 7.0.6 via package.json overrides
# (verified in node_modules/cross-spawn/package.json). Trivy still reports
# the older spec string from a deep transitive's package.json — same
# dep-spec-string artifact as the tar entries above.
CVE-2024-21538
